-- Shaw Ex-Chief to Get $5.95 Million a Year Pension Plan, Globe Reports
-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 2010-12-14T11:33:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-14/shaw-ex-chief-to-get-5-95-million-a-year-pension-globe-reports.html
Shaw Communication’s Inc.’s board
voted to increase the pension payable to Jim Shaw, 53, who
retired as chief executive officer in November, to $495,833 a
month, or $5.95 million a year, the Globe & Mail reported,
citing documents sent to shareholders.  Shaw’s father, J.R. Shaw, the chairman of the Canadian
cable and satellite television and Internet company, receives a
$5.4 million annual pension, the newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
